original: Enewald, Nils, lektor, Linköping, f. 16/11/88 i Tryde, Krist. 1. G. 32 m. Martha Stenberg. — Stud:ex. i Lund 09, fil. kand. där 12, fil. mag. 13, foliksk:lär:ex. 14, fil. lic. 18, fil. dr 21, provår i Sthlm 16. Stud:res. t. Danm., Norge o. Tyskl. Vik. adj. i Växjö 14-15 o. 17, e. o. lektor i Eksjö 17-22, adj. i Hälsingborg 21, lär. i sv. v. Hälsingborgs hand:gymn. 22-25, lektor i hist. o. modersm. v. Linköp. h. a. 1. sed. 25. RNO.
translated: Enewald, Nils, lecturer, Linköping, born November 16th, 1888 in Tryde, Kristianstad. Married in 1932 to Martha Stenberg. He graduated from Lund with a high school diploma in 1909 and a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1912, followed by a Master of Arts degree in 1913, teaching certificate in 1914, a licentiate degree in 1918, and a doctorate in 1921. He spent a probationary year in Stockholm in 1916 and studied abroad in Denmark, Norway, and Germany. He served as a temporary assistant in Växjö from 1914-1915 and 1917, and an acting lecturer in Eksjö from 1917-1922. He was an assistant teacher in Hälsingborg in 1921 and a teacher of Swedish and physical education at Hälsingborg's Handelsgymnasium from 1922-1925. He has been a lecturer in history and Swedish language at Linköping since 1925. He is a member of the Royal Order of the North Star.
